results.name: T(n,k) is the number of labeled connected posets of n labeled elements with k covering relations (n>=1, k>=0). Triangle read by rows.
link: Index entries for sequences related to posets
example: There are 8 connected unlabeled Hasse diagrams on 4 nodes with 3 arcs. 4 of them have automorphism group order 1, 2 of them have automorphism group order 2 and 2 have order 6. So T(4,3) = 4*4!/1 + 2*4!/2 + 2*4!/6 = 128.
There are 2 connected unlabeled Hasse diagrams on 4 nodes with 4 arcs, one has automorphism group order 2, the other 4. So T(4,4) = 1*4!/2+1*4!/4 = 18.
xref: Cf. A001927 (row sums), A342589 (not necessarily connected), A342590 (unlabeled).
